<document xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:z="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/z" source="Whatizit"><text><SENT sid="0" pm="."><plain><z:e sem="disease" ids="C0268390" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="">Muckle-Wells syndrome</z:e> (MWS) is a rare condition characterized by <z:hpo ids='HP_0001025'>urticaria</z:hpo>, <z:hpo ids='HP_0002829'>arthralgias</z:hpo>, <z:hpo ids='HP_0000365'>deafness</z:hpo> and amyloid <z:hpo ids='HP_0000112'>nephropathy</z:hpo> </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="1" pm="."><plain>The <z:hpo ids='HP_0003040'>arthropathy</z:hpo> is poorly documented </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="2" pm="."><plain>We describe the <z:hpo ids='HP_0003040'>arthropathy</z:hpo> occurring in four cases of MWS and discuss the management </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="3" pm="."><plain>Each patient developed recurrent bouts of transient <z:hpo ids='HP_0100769'>synovitis</z:hpo> </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="4" pm="."><plain>One patient developed a persistent <z:mp ids='MP_0001924'>sterile</z:mp> <z:e sem="disease" ids="C1692886" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="">pyoarthrosis</z:e> </plain></SENT>
</text></document>